Collections are arranged into groups for searching. Click on a group name to search the collections in that group. A collection may include some content outside of the group's definition, and a collection could appear in more than one group. Click the title of a specific collection to search it alone. Sometimes it is advantageous to search a single collection. For example, search field and sorting options are often specific to the collection, allowing for a more refined search.

Some collections have a very narrow focus. Other collections are broader, and may encompass many sub-collections. Occassionally an image appears in multiple collections, though generally there is a single authoritative source for each image.

Punctuation: All punctuation is treated as an empty space.
Case: The search engine is not case sensitive.
Wildcards: Use wildcard * to expand word stems. This is a good way to search for variations on a word.
Choose image collections: Limit your search to only those collections you choose in the image collections list.

Facets.Query: select SQL_CALC_FOUND_ROWS concat('S-clark1ic8lift-X-',clark1ic8lift_media.m_id,']',clark1ic8lift_media.m_iid ) as `id` , NULL as `sortval` from clark1ic8lift left join clark1ic8lift_media on clark1ic8lift.ic_id = clark1ic8lift_media.m_id where ( ( match (`ic_all`) against ('+clark1ic' in boolean mode) ) ) And clark1ic8lift_media.m_searchable = '1'

select istruct_isentryid, concat('S-clark1ic8lift-X-',clark1ic8lift_media.m_id,']',clark1ic8lift_media.m_iid ) as `id` , NULL as `sortval` from clark1ic8lift left join clark1ic8lift_media on clark1ic8lift.ic_id = clark1ic8lift_media.m_id where ( ( match (`ic_all`) against ('+clark1ic' in boolean mode) ) ) And clark1ic8lift_media.m_searchable = '1'

SELECT b.field, b.value, COUNT(b.value) AS total FROM ItemBrowse b, ( select istruct_isentryid, concat('S-clark1ic8lift-X-',clark1ic8lift_media.m_id,']',clark1ic8lift_media.m_iid ) as `id` , NULL as `sortval` from clark1ic8lift left join clark1ic8lift_media on clark1ic8lift.ic_id = clark1ic8lift_media.m_id where ( ( match (`ic_all`) against ('+clark1ic' in boolean mode) ) ) And clark1ic8lift_media.m_searchable = '1' ) a WHERE b.collid = ? AND a.istruct_isentryid = b.idno GROUP BY b.field, b.value ORDER BY b.field, total DESC, b.value
